<h2><strong>What is hibiscus tea?</strong></h2>
AÂ rich ruby red concoction can be made from these sepals of the roselle (scientific name hibiscus sabdariffa) plant.Â The tea tastes slightly sour, a bit like cranberry juice and is rich in organic acids, antioxidants and flavonoids. It boosts immunity, metabolism and cardiovascular function. Moreover, it is low calorie and caffeine free.
